00:33:19.030 --> 00:33:22.360
So you mentioned that it's
important to void expecting

00:33:22.360 --> 00:33:26.320
some outcome, or
something that comes back,

00:33:26.320 --> 00:33:29.920
so I know about myself and
about some other people,

00:33:29.920 --> 00:33:33.455
that a lot of people actually
feel that something is missing.

00:33:33.455 --> 00:33:37.660
We want this,
we're missing that.

00:33:37.660 --> 00:33:40.440
Any tips on how to
avoid expectations,

00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:45.450
about how to avoid expecting
a return, something in return.

00:33:47.620 --> 00:33:49.370
DAYAMRITA CHAITANYA:
Correct me if I'm not

00:33:49.370 --> 00:33:50.390
answering you properly.

00:33:54.090 --> 00:33:57.990
There's beautiful
words in Bhagavad Gita

00:33:57.990 --> 00:34:01.770
says you should do
your action and don't

00:34:01.770 --> 00:34:03.850
worry about the result.

00:34:03.850 --> 00:34:07.090
So without expecting
the result, you're

00:34:07.090 --> 00:34:09.159
not going to do an action.

00:34:09.159 --> 00:34:09.658
Correct?

00:34:13.010 --> 00:34:17.580
But the thing is, I'll tell
you an example of this.

00:34:17.580 --> 00:34:20.770
For example, you are
going to meet a friend

00:34:20.770 --> 00:34:23.239
and ask him for some
money because you're

00:34:23.239 --> 00:34:27.510
in need of money, so
you want like $2,000.

00:34:27.510 --> 00:34:28.770
Correct?

00:34:28.770 --> 00:34:32.600
So what happens is, I'm
just saying an example,

00:34:32.600 --> 00:34:38.060
and what happens is he
can give you $2,000,

00:34:38.060 --> 00:34:41.239
or sometimes if he's
in a very happy mood he

00:34:41.239 --> 00:34:45.400
says oh, take $4,000 and
don't worry, don't return it.

00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:50.600
Or the other thing is he
can say, I have only $1,000,

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:54.460
I don't have money, or he could
say I was going to come to you

00:34:54.460 --> 00:34:57.410
and ask money from you.

00:34:57.410 --> 00:34:58.060
Correct?

00:34:58.060 --> 00:35:02.200
So there are
different scenarios,

00:35:11.070 --> 00:35:14.610
Selfless expectation
means expectation thinking

00:35:14.610 --> 00:35:16.590
about the possible outcomes.

00:35:19.640 --> 00:35:22.240
So what happens is
the beauty of that

00:35:22.240 --> 00:35:28.190
is because whatever outcome
that comes, you're not depressed

00:35:28.190 --> 00:35:29.870
or you're not
crying, you are not

00:35:29.870 --> 00:35:33.190
worrying about what the
outcome is, because you already

00:35:33.190 --> 00:35:36.740
know that you're
already expecting

00:35:36.740 --> 00:35:39.760
what the expectation would be.

00:35:39.760 --> 00:35:43.260
So it's kind of just
trying to understand

00:35:43.260 --> 00:35:47.030
what will be the results
of your expectations.

00:35:47.030 --> 00:35:52.280
I'm not saying that you should
not have expectations, so just

00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:58.290
have an awareness that
whatever expectation,

00:35:58.290 --> 00:36:01.040
there are different
forms of results to that.

00:36:03.550 --> 00:36:08.710
So I'll just do a very
quick two to three minutes,

00:36:08.710 --> 00:36:12.080
so kindly said straight.

00:36:12.080 --> 00:36:16.410
Before you close your eyes,
try to look at the ceiling

00:36:16.410 --> 00:36:26.420
or just have a vacant stare
and slowly try and become

00:36:26.420 --> 00:36:31.220
aware of your breathing
process inside

00:36:31.220 --> 00:36:33.000
and whatever is happening
inside the body.

00:36:38.450 --> 00:36:42.000
Let's try to follow each
and every inhalation

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:46.100
and exhalation
that occurs within,

00:36:46.100 --> 00:36:48.450
and try to breathe normally.

00:36:53.240 --> 00:36:58.890
And as you slowly and
slowly breathe and become

00:36:58.890 --> 00:37:07.390
aware and more and more aware
of your breath and the process

00:37:07.390 --> 00:37:12.870
your eyes will slowly
close without any effort

00:37:12.870 --> 00:37:13.820
from your part.

00:37:19.190 --> 00:37:21.235
Then you feel
completely relaxed.

00:37:37.450 --> 00:37:42.620
And slowly start
feeling the light--

00:37:42.620 --> 00:37:44.580
area of light
inside your heart--

00:37:48.490 --> 00:37:50.920
Which is the center of the
body, not the physical heart,

00:37:50.920 --> 00:37:52.050
but the spiritual heart.

00:38:00.830 --> 00:38:10.120
And as the light slowly
starts spreading and filling

00:38:10.120 --> 00:38:15.190
your whole being,
imagine that you're

00:38:15.190 --> 00:38:20.489
being filled with love,
with bliss, with peace,

00:38:20.489 --> 00:38:21.155
with compassion.

00:38:27.770 --> 00:38:32.640
And feel each and
every cell in your body

00:38:32.640 --> 00:38:33.875
being filled with that light.

00:38:46.930 --> 00:38:51.880
And feel every cell
reverberating with love,

00:38:51.880 --> 00:38:53.300
with peace and with compassion.

00:39:08.990 --> 00:39:16.730
And imagine your whole
being completely immersed

00:39:16.730 --> 00:39:21.716
and just becoming one with
that light, and only the light

00:39:21.716 --> 00:39:22.216
exists.

00:39:28.720 --> 00:39:34.870
Now visualize the light
going from your heart

00:39:34.870 --> 00:39:40.500
towards the whole world, to
all the beings in this world,

00:39:40.500 --> 00:39:43.930
to the nature, just like
the rays of the sun.

00:39:47.360 --> 00:39:51.140
And imagine this light, just
like the rays of the sun,

00:39:51.140 --> 00:39:55.100
going out to all the beings,
and as the light falls

00:39:55.100 --> 00:39:58.760
on each and every
being, imagine they also

00:39:58.760 --> 00:40:02.447
become more loving,
more peaceful, and more

00:40:02.447 --> 00:40:03.030
compassionate.

00:40:07.420 --> 00:40:12.200
And imagine this whole world
and this whole universe

00:40:12.200 --> 00:40:15.960
to be filled with the light of
love, peace, and compassion.

